{"title_page": "A Soldier's Heart", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = A Soldier's Heart\n| image                    = ASoldiersHeartTitleCard.jpg\n| caption                  = Title card\n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Action film|Action]]\n* [[Military fiction]]\n}}\n| creator                  = [[Charo Santos-Concio]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = {{Plainlist|\n* Jerry B. Gracio\n* [[Carlo Katigbak]]\n* Chie Floresca\n* Chino Nicanor\n* April L. Jalandra\n}}\n| director                 = Richard V. Somes\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Gerald Anderson]]\n* [[Carlo Aquino]]\n* [[Vin Abrenica]]\n* [[Elmo Magalona]]\n* [[Jerome Ponce]]\n* [[Yves Flores]]\n* [[Nash Aguas]]\n* [[Sue Ramirez]]\n}}\n| opentheme          = \n| composer           = \n| country            = [[Philippines]]\n| language           = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| num_seasons        = 1<!--Only increment as a new season premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| num_episodes       = 40<!--As of March 13, 2020--><!--Please do not update the episode count daily, the episodes will be updated WEEKLY so that only a single edit is necessary-->\n| list_episodes      = List of A Soldier's Heart episodes\n| executive_producer = Marielle de Guzman-Navarro\n| producer           = \n| cinematography     = \n| editor             = {{ubl|Joy C. Buenaventura|Dennis A. Salgado}}\n| runtime            = \n| location           = [[Philippines]]\n| company            = RCD Narratives\n| distributor        = \n| network            = [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n| picture_format     = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|2020|1|20}}\n| last_aired         = {{End date|2020|3|13}} ''({{small|on-hiatus}})''\n| preceded_by        = \n| related            = \n| website            = http://asoldiersheart.abs-cbn.com/\n}}\n\n'''''A Soldier's Heart''''' is a 2020 [[Philippine television drama|Philippine drama]] [[television series]] starring [[Gerald Anderson]], [[Carlo Aquino]], [[Vin Abrenica]], [[Elmo Magalona]], [[Jerome Ponce]], [[Yves Flores]], [[Nash Aguas]] and [[Sue Ramirez]]. The series premiered on [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]'s ''Primetime Bida'' evening block and worldwide via [[The Filipino Channel]] on January 20, 2020, replacing ''[[The Killer Bride]]''.<!-- Do not add grammar anymore --><!-- No reference is needed here if the content is already sourced in the body of the article per WP:CITELEAD! -->\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe series primarily focuses on the soldiers of the [[4th Infantry Division (Philippines)|4th Infantry Division]] of the [[Philippine Army]] and their actions during combat. Through multiple perspectives, the story focuses on these soldiers, mainly: Alex Marasigan ([[Gerald Anderson]]), an IT expert who quits his desk job and joins because just like his brother, he wants to serve the country, Abraham \"Abe\" Kamlun ([[Carlo Aquino]]), a Tausug Muslim man, who, despite his family's opposition of the move, joins the Army nonetheless, and Michael Mendoza ([[Nash Aguas]]), a boy who joins the Army to provide for his family. \n\nThe series also focuses on their [[Moro insurgency in the Philippines|Moro]] [[separatist]] adversaries, led by Saal Alhuraji ([[Sid Lucero]]), also known by his [[nom de guerre]] ''Abdul Waajid'', who seeks to avenge his father who was killed by the military.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Gerald Anderson by Ronn Tan, April 2010.png\n|caption1 = Gerald Anderson portrays Alex Marasigan.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Elmo Magalona.jpg\n|caption2 = Elmo Magalona portrays Jethro Mondejar.\n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = Yves Flores.jpg\n|caption3 = Yves Flores portrays Benjie Arguelles.\n|width3 = 150\n|image4 = Nash-Aguas.jpg\n|caption4 = Nash Aguas portrays Michael Mendoza.\n|width4 = 150\n|image5 = Ariel solo.jpg\n|caption5 = Ariel Rivera portrays Victor Mondejar.\n|width5 = 150\n}}\n===Main===\n* [[Gerald Anderson]]<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/7/24/news/cast-ng-a-soldiers-heart-ipinakilala-na-51186|title=Cast ng ''A Soldier's Heart'', ipinakilala na!|website=ABS-CBN Entertainment|date=July 24, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Training\">{{cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/pilipino-star-ngayon/showbiz/2019/08/11/1942453/sumabak-sa-scout-ranger-training-gerald-kumain-na-nakadapa-habang-nasa-putikan|title=Sumabak sa Scout Ranger training, Gerald kumain na nakadapa habang nasa putikan!|website=Philippine Star|date=August 11, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Brotherhood\">{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DA83eI2g0ec|title=A Soldier's Heart: The Brotherhood Teaser|website=ABS-CBN Entertainment|date=January 9, 2020|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/2020/1/17/a-soldiers-heart-shows-sacrifice-loyal-brother?lang=en|title=''A Soldier's Heart'' shows sacrifice, loyal brotherhood of soldiers|work=ABS-CBN Corporate|date=January 17, 2020|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}</ref> as Pvt. Alexander \"Alex\" Marasigan / Hakeem Alhuraji\n* [[Carlo Aquino]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Abraham \"Abe\" Kamlun\n* [[Vin Abrenica]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 1st Lt. Elmer Marasigan\n* [[Elmo Magalona]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 1st Lt. Jethro Mondejar\n* [[Jerome Ponce]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Philip \"Phil\" Panganiban\n* [[Yves Flores]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Benjamin \"Benjie\" Arguelles\n* [[Nash Aguas]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Michael \"Striker\" Mendoza\n* [[Sue Ramirez]]<ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://showbizchika.net/sue-ramirez-and-gerald-anderson-gear-up-for-upcoming-series-a-soldiers-heart/|title=Sue Ramirez and Gerald Anderson gear up for upcoming series ''A Soldier's Heart''|website=Showbiz Chika}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 2nd Lt. Lourdes \"Lourd\" Bacalso\n\n===Supporting===\n* [[Sid Lucero]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Saal Alhuraji/Abdul Waajid\n* [[Ariel Rivera]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as BGen. Victor C. Mondejar\n* [[Rommel Padilla]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as BGen. Dante G. Marasigan\n* [[Irma Adlawan]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Yasmin Alhuraji/Amara\n* [[Raymond Bagatsing]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Col. Melicio Adriano\n* [[Mickey Ferriols]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Minda Marasigan\n* [[Mon Confiado]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Maj. Raul R. Lucente\n* [[Nikki Valdez]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Fatima Alhuraji\n* [[Matt Evans]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/07/31/19/with-star-magic-return-matt-evans-feels-his-prayers-were-answered|title=With Star Magic return, Matt Evans feels his prayers were answered|website=ABS-CBN News|date=July 31, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Rasheed Amad\n* Nor Domingo<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Col. Virgilio I. Fontiveros\n* Angelo Ilagan as Pvt. Gregorio \"Gorio\" Salud\n* Isay Alvarez<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Maysam Kamlun\n* Jun Hidalgo as Ahmed Kamlun\n* [[Claire Ruiz]] as Grace Alfonso \n* Royce Cabrera as Pvt. Andy Alfonso \n;Introducing\n* Charlie Dizon as Isabel Gezali<!--stiop adding two spelling for Isabel. It doesn't make sense for one to be a first name and the other a nickname when they are uttered the same way-->\n* Patrick Quiroz<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Amir Majul\n\n===Guests===\n* Kiko Matos as Akir \n* Zeppi Borromeo as Nassir \n* [[Roxanne Guinoo]] as Mrs. Arguelles \n* [[Pen Medina]] as Mr. Panganiban\n* Ruby Ruiz \n* John Vincent Servilla as Chino Villaverde\n* Kokoy de Jesus\n* Lorenzo Martinez\n* [[Simon Ibarra]]\n* [[Mercedes Cabral]]\n* Bing Davao as [[Secretary of National Defense (Philippines)|Defense Secretary]]\n* [[Mari Kaimo]] as [[President of the Philippines|President]]\n* Richard Quan as Gov. Amer Gezali\n* Sammie Rimando as Chloe Gezali\n* Jerry O'Hara as \n* Levi Ignacio as Congressman Shakiri\n* Marco Masa as young Saal\n* Vash Paras as young Hakeem/Alex\n* [[Ketchup Eusebio]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Cpl. Olan Arguelles\n* [[Lito Pimentel]] as Yosef Alhuraji\n* [[Boom Labrusca]]\n* Arnold Reyes as Pinong\n* Teroy de Guzman as Abdul Waajid\n* Minco Fabregas as Jamal\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe series airs on ABS-CBN's ''Primetime Bida'' evening block and worldwide on The Filipino Channel at 9:20 PM (PST).\n\nOn March 16, 2020, the show was put on hiatus due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|Wuhan coronavirus pandemic]]. Its timeslot was temporarily filled by ''[[Wildflower (TV series)|Wildflower]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/150320/abs-cbn-wildflower-gma-7-my-husband-lover-new-primetime-line-up-a724-20200323|title=ABS-CBN's Wildflower goes head-to-head with GMA-7's My Husband's Lover in new primetime line-up|last=Anarcon|first=James Patrick|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal|PEP]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> ''[[iWant#List of original programs|iWant Originals]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/03/14/20/read-abs-cbn-statement-on-special-primetime-programming-amid-metro-manila-quarantine|title=READ: ABS-CBN statement on special primetime programming amid Metro Manila quarantine|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=March 14, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> and ''[[Tubig at Langis]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ent.abs-cbn.com/tubig-at-langis/articles-news/1390316-review-love-transcends-in-tubig-at-langis-finale-9528/amp|title=\u201cTubig at Langis\" back on ABS-CBN, airs weeknights on primetime|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN Corporate]]|date=April 14, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{{Infobox Kantar rating\n| timeslot        = 9:15PM\n| pilot_rating    = 19.8%\n| pilot_date      = {{dts|2020|1|20}}\n| pilot_ref       = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/tv-ratings/2020/1/22/national-tv-ratings-january-20-21-2020?lang=en|title=National TV Ratings (January 20\u201321, 2020)|work=ABS-CBN Corporate|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| finale_rating   = TBD\n| finale_date     = \n| finale_ref      =\n| peak_rating     = TBD <!-- If you add a high rating when the series ends. -->\n| peak_date       =\n| peak_ref        =\n| average_rating  = TBD\n| average_ref     =\n}}\n\n===Controversies===\n====Depiction of Butuan City====\nThe show came under fire early in the show's run for its perceived \"unrealistic\" and \"offensive\" depiction of [[Butuan City]].<ref name=\"PilotBlues\">{{cite news|url=https://amp.rappler.com/entertainment/news/250004-a-soldiers-heart-shows-unreal-depiction-butuan-city-says-agusan-congressman|title=A Soldier\u2019s Heart\u2019 shows \u2018unreal depiction\u2019 of Butuan City, says Agusan del Norte rep|publisher=[[Rappler]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> The scene in question was from the show's pilot episode showing the bombing of a market in the city.<ref name=\"PilotBlues\"/> In a statement, [[Agusan del Norte]] 1st District Representative [[Lawrence Fortun]]  asked ABS-CBN \u201cto immediately air an appropriate disclaimer, review and reconsider the content and story elements of the teleserye in order not to further besmirch the reputation of our historic city.\u201d<ref name=\"PilotBlues\"/>\n\nABS-CBN, for its part, apologized on January 23, 2020. Its statement read:  \u201cABS-CBN would like to apologize to Agusan Del Norte Rep. Lawrence Fortun and the people of Butuan City if the scenes in the TV series \u2018A Soldier\u2019s Heart\u2019 have offended them. While the incident portrayed in the series was fictitious, there was mention of the city name.\u201d\n\n\u201cWe would like to assure them that there was no deliberate intention to portray Butuan City negatively in the show. We acknowledge that Butuan is one of the most beautiful and peaceful cities in the country,\u201d it added.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/amp/entertainment/01/23/20/abs-cbn-sorry-after-butuan-solon-complains-against-a-soldiers-heart|title=ABS-CBN sorry after Butuan solon complains against 'A Soldier\u2019s Heart'|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 24, 2020, ABS-CBN executives headed by Cory Vidanes and Laurenti Dyogi met with Fortun to further clear the issue. After said meeting, Fortun noted that aside from airing specific disclaimers, ABS-CBN has removed all production elements, scenes, and references that may be offensive to Butuan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/148970/abs-cbn-removes-offensive-butuan-scenes-from-a-soldier-s-heart-a771-20200127|title=ABS-CBN removes \"offensive\" Butuan scenes from A Soldier's Heart|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal|PEP]]|first=Mari-An|last=Santos|date=January 26, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of programs broadcast by ABS-CBN]]\n* [[List of ABS-CBN drama series]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://asoldiersheart.abs-cbn.com/}}\n\n{{ABS-CBN (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n{{ABS-CBN drama series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Soldier's Heart, A}}\n[[Category:ABS-CBN drama series]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:Philippine military television series]]\n[[Category:2020 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Television production suspended due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = A Soldier's Heart\n| image                    = ASoldiersHeartTitleCard.jpg\n| caption                  = Title card\n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Action film|Action]]\n* [[Military fiction]]\n}}\n| creator                  = [[Charo Santos-Concio]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = {{Plainlist|\n* Jerry B. Gracio\n* [[Carlo Katigbak]]\n* Chie Floresca\n* Chino Nicanor\n* April L. Jalandra\n}}\n| director                 = Richard V. Somes\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Gerald Anderson]]\n* [[Carlo Aquino]]\n* [[Vin Abrenica]]\n* [[Elmo Magalona]]\n* [[Jerome Ponce]]\n* [[Yves Flores]]\n* [[Nash Aguas]]\n* [[Sue Ramirez]]\n}}\n| opentheme          = \n| composer           = \n| country            = [[Philippines]]\n| language           = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| num_seasons        = 1<!--Only increment as a new season premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| num_episodes       = 40<!--As of March 13, 2020--><!--Please do not update the episode count daily, the episodes will be updated WEEKLY so that only a single edit is necessary-->\n| list_episodes      = List of A Soldier's Heart episodes\n| executive_producer = Marielle de Guzman-Navarro\n| producer           = \n| cinematography     = \n| editor             = {{ubl|Joy C. Buenaventura|Dennis A. Salgado}}\n| runtime            = \n| location           = [[Philippines]]\n| company            = RCD Narratives\n| distributor        = \n| network            = [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n| picture_format     = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|2020|1|20}}\n| last_aired         = {{End date|2020|3|13}} ''({{small|on-hiatus}})''\n| preceded_by        = \n| related            = \n| website            = http://asoldiersheart.abs-cbn.com/\n}}\n\n'''''A Soldier's Heart''''' is a 2020 [[Philippine television drama|Philippine drama]] [[television series]] starring [[Gerald Anderson]], [[Carlo Aquino]], [[Vin Abrenica]], [[Elmo Magalona]], [[Jerome Ponce]], [[Yves Flores]], [[Nash Aguas]] and [[Sue Ramirez]]. The series premiered on [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]'s ''Primetime Bida'' evening block and worldwide via [[The Filipino Channel]] on January 20, 2020, replacing ''[[The Killer Bride]]''.<!-- Do not add grammar anymore --><!-- No reference is needed here if the content is already sourced in the body of the article per WP:CITELEAD! -->\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe series primarily focuses on the soldiers of the [[4th Infantry Division (Philippines)|4th Infantry Division]] of the [[Philippine Army]] and their actions during combat. Through multiple perspectives, the story focuses on these soldiers, mainly: Alex Marasigan ([[Gerald Anderson]]), an IT expert who quits his desk job and joins because just like his brother, he wants to serve the country, Abraham \"Abe\" Kamlun ([[Carlo Aquino]]), a Tausug Muslim man, who, despite his family's opposition of the move, joins the Army nonetheless, and Michael Mendoza ([[Nash Aguas]]), a boy who joins the Army to provide for his family. \n\nThe series also focuses on their [[Moro]] [[separatist]] adversaries, led by Saal Alhuraji ([[Sid Lucero]]), also known by his [[nom de guerre]] ''Abdul Waajid'', who seeks to avenge his father who was killed by the military.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Gerald Anderson by Ronn Tan, April 2010.png\n|caption1 = Gerald Anderson portrays Alex Marasigan.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Elmo Magalona.jpg\n|caption2 = Elmo Magalona portrays Jethro Mondejar.\n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = Yves Flores.jpg\n|caption3 = Yves Flores portrays Benjie Arguelles.\n|width3 = 150\n|image4 = Nash-Aguas.jpg\n|caption4 = Nash Aguas portrays Michael Mendoza.\n|width4 = 150\n|image5 = Ariel solo.jpg\n|caption5 = Ariel Rivera portrays Victor Mondejar.\n|width5 = 150\n}}\n===Main===\n* [[Gerald Anderson]]<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/7/24/news/cast-ng-a-soldiers-heart-ipinakilala-na-51186|title=Cast ng ''A Soldier's Heart'', ipinakilala na!|website=ABS-CBN Entertainment|date=July 24, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Training\">{{cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/pilipino-star-ngayon/showbiz/2019/08/11/1942453/sumabak-sa-scout-ranger-training-gerald-kumain-na-nakadapa-habang-nasa-putikan|title=Sumabak sa Scout Ranger training, Gerald kumain na nakadapa habang nasa putikan!|website=Philippine Star|date=August 11, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Brotherhood\">{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DA83eI2g0ec|title=A Soldier's Heart: The Brotherhood Teaser|website=ABS-CBN Entertainment|date=January 9, 2020|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/2020/1/17/a-soldiers-heart-shows-sacrifice-loyal-brother?lang=en|title=''A Soldier's Heart'' shows sacrifice, loyal brotherhood of soldiers|work=ABS-CBN Corporate|date=January 17, 2020|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}</ref> as Pvt. Alexander \"Alex\" Marasigan / Hakeem Alhuraji\n* [[Carlo Aquino]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Abraham \"Abe\" Kamlun\n* [[Vin Abrenica]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 1st Lt. Elmer Marasigan\n* [[Elmo Magalona]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 1st Lt. Jethro Mondejar\n* [[Jerome Ponce]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Philip \"Phil\" Panganiban\n* [[Yves Flores]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Benjamin \"Benjie\" Arguelles\n* [[Nash Aguas]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/><ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Pvt. Michael \"Striker\" Mendoza\n* [[Sue Ramirez]]<ref name=\"Brotherhood\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://showbizchika.net/sue-ramirez-and-gerald-anderson-gear-up-for-upcoming-series-a-soldiers-heart/|title=Sue Ramirez and Gerald Anderson gear up for upcoming series ''A Soldier's Heart''|website=Showbiz Chika}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as 2nd Lt. Lourdes \"Lourd\" Bacalso\n\n===Supporting===\n* [[Sid Lucero]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Saal Alhuraji/Abdul Waajid\n* [[Ariel Rivera]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as BGen. Victor C. Mondejar\n* [[Rommel Padilla]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as BGen. Dante G. Marasigan\n* [[Irma Adlawan]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Yasmin Alhuraji/Amara\n* [[Raymond Bagatsing]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Col. Melicio Adriano\n* [[Mickey Ferriols]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Minda Marasigan\n* [[Mon Confiado]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Maj. Raul R. Lucente\n* [[Nikki Valdez]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Fatima Alhuraji\n* [[Matt Evans]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/07/31/19/with-star-magic-return-matt-evans-feels-his-prayers-were-answered|title=With Star Magic return, Matt Evans feels his prayers were answered|website=ABS-CBN News|date=July 31, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Rasheed Amad\n* Nor Domingo<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Col. Virgilio I. Fontiveros\n* Angelo Ilagan as Pvt. Gregorio \"Gorio\" Salud\n* Isay Alvarez<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Maysam Kamlun\n* Jun Hidalgo as Ahmed Kamlun\n* [[Claire Ruiz]] as Grace Alfonso \n* Royce Cabrera as Pvt. Andy Alfonso \n;Introducing\n* Charlie Dizon as Isabel Gezali<!--stiop adding two spelling for Isabel. It doesn't make sense for one to be a first name and the other a nickname when they are uttered the same way-->\n* Patrick Quiroz<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Amir Majul\n\n===Guests===\n* Kiko Matos as Akir \n* Zeppi Borromeo as Nassir \n* [[Roxanne Guinoo]] as Mrs. Arguelles \n* [[Pen Medina]] as Mr. Panganiban\n* Ruby Ruiz \n* John Vincent Servilla as Chino Villaverde\n* Kokoy de Jesus\n* Lorenzo Martinez\n* [[Simon Ibarra]]\n* [[Mercedes Cabral]]\n* Bing Davao as [[Secretary of National Defense (Philippines)|Defense Secretary]]\n* [[Mari Kaimo]] as [[President of the Philippines|President]]\n* Richard Quan as Gov. Amer Gezali\n* Sammie Rimando as Chloe Gezali\n* Jerry O'Hara as \n* Levi Ignacio as Congressman Shakiri\n* Marco Masa as young Saal\n* Vash Paras as young Hakeem/Alex\n* [[Ketchup Eusebio]]<ref name=\"ASHCast\"/> as Cpl. Olan Arguelles\n* [[Lito Pimentel]] as Yosef Alhuraji\n* [[Boom Labrusca]]\n* Arnold Reyes as Pinong\n* Teroy de Guzman as Abdul Waajid\n* Minco Fabregas as Jamal\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe series airs on ABS-CBN's ''Primetime Bida'' evening block and worldwide on The Filipino Channel at 9:20 PM (PST).\n\nOn March 16, 2020, the show was put on hiatus due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|Wuhan coronavirus pandemic]]. Its timeslot was temporarily filled by ''[[Wildflower (TV series)|Wildflower]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/150320/abs-cbn-wildflower-gma-7-my-husband-lover-new-primetime-line-up-a724-20200323|title=ABS-CBN's Wildflower goes head-to-head with GMA-7's My Husband's Lover in new primetime line-up|last=Anarcon|first=James Patrick|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal|PEP]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> ''[[iWant#List of original programs|iWant Originals]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/03/14/20/read-abs-cbn-statement-on-special-primetime-programming-amid-metro-manila-quarantine|title=READ: ABS-CBN statement on special primetime programming amid Metro Manila quarantine|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=March 14, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> and ''[[Tubig at Langis]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ent.abs-cbn.com/tubig-at-langis/articles-news/1390316-review-love-transcends-in-tubig-at-langis-finale-9528/amp|title=\u201cTubig at Langis\" back on ABS-CBN, airs weeknights on primetime|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN Corporate]]|date=April 14, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{{Infobox Kantar rating\n| timeslot        = 9:15PM\n| pilot_rating    = 19.8%\n| pilot_date      = {{dts|2020|1|20}}\n| pilot_ref       = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/tv-ratings/2020/1/22/national-tv-ratings-january-20-21-2020?lang=en|title=National TV Ratings (January 20\u201321, 2020)|work=ABS-CBN Corporate|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| finale_rating   = TBD\n| finale_date     = \n| finale_ref      =\n| peak_rating     = TBD <!-- If you add a high rating when the series ends. -->\n| peak_date       =\n| peak_ref        =\n| average_rating  = TBD\n| average_ref     =\n}}\n\n===Controversies===\n====Depiction of Butuan City====\nThe show came under fire early in the show's run for its perceived \"unrealistic\" and \"offensive\" depiction of [[Butuan City]].<ref name=\"PilotBlues\">{{cite news|url=https://amp.rappler.com/entertainment/news/250004-a-soldiers-heart-shows-unreal-depiction-butuan-city-says-agusan-congressman|title=A Soldier\u2019s Heart\u2019 shows \u2018unreal depiction\u2019 of Butuan City, says Agusan del Norte rep|publisher=[[Rappler]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> The scene in question was from the show's pilot episode showing the bombing of a market in the city.<ref name=\"PilotBlues\"/> In a statement, [[Agusan del Norte]] 1st District Representative [[Lawrence Fortun]]  asked ABS-CBN \u201cto immediately air an appropriate disclaimer, review and reconsider the content and story elements of the teleserye in order not to further besmirch the reputation of our historic city.\u201d<ref name=\"PilotBlues\"/>\n\nABS-CBN, for its part, apologized on January 23, 2020. Its statement read:  \u201cABS-CBN would like to apologize to Agusan Del Norte Rep. Lawrence Fortun and the people of Butuan City if the scenes in the TV series \u2018A Soldier\u2019s Heart\u2019 have offended them. While the incident portrayed in the series was fictitious, there was mention of the city name.\u201d\n\n\u201cWe would like to assure them that there was no deliberate intention to portray Butuan City negatively in the show. We acknowledge that Butuan is one of the most beautiful and peaceful cities in the country,\u201d it added.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/amp/entertainment/01/23/20/abs-cbn-sorry-after-butuan-solon-complains-against-a-soldiers-heart|title=ABS-CBN sorry after Butuan solon complains against 'A Soldier\u2019s Heart'|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 24, 2020, ABS-CBN executives headed by Cory Vidanes and Laurenti Dyogi met with Fortun to further clear the issue. After said meeting, Fortun noted that aside from airing specific disclaimers, ABS-CBN has removed all production elements, scenes, and references that may be offensive to Butuan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/148970/abs-cbn-removes-offensive-butuan-scenes-from-a-soldier-s-heart-a771-20200127|title=ABS-CBN removes \"offensive\" Butuan scenes from A Soldier's Heart|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal|PEP]]|first=Mari-An|last=Santos|date=January 26, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of programs broadcast by ABS-CBN]]\n* [[List of ABS-CBN drama series]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://asoldiersheart.abs-cbn.com/}}\n\n{{ABS-CBN (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n{{ABS-CBN drama series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Soldier's Heart, A}}\n[[Category:ABS-CBN drama series]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:Philippine military television series]]\n[[Category:2020 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Filipino-lan